# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the LedgerMind Next.js project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Package**: `@vercel/speed-insights@2.0.0`
- **Package Manager**: pnpm
- **Command**: `pnpm i @vercel/speed-insights`

### 2. Files Modified

#### `app/layout.tsx`
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout, placed at the end of the `<body>` tag
- This follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js 13.5+ with App Router

#### `package.json`
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights@2.0.0` to dependencies

#### `pnpm-lock.yaml` (new file)
- Created lockfile to ensure consistent dependency resolution across environments

## Implementation Details

### Framework Detection
- Identified project as **Next.js 14.2** with App Router
- Used the framework-specific installation instructions for Next.js from the official Vercel documentation

### Configuration Approach
- Followed the official Vercel Speed Insights quickstart guide (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart)
- Placed the `<SpeedInsights />` component in the root layout (`app/layout.tsx`) as recommended for Next.js App Router
- The component is placed at the end of the body tag to ensure it doesn't block rendering of main content

### Build Verification
- Successfully built the project with `pnpm build`
- No TypeScript errors introduced
- Build completed without warnings
- Static pages generated successfully

## Next Steps

To complete the Speed Insights setup:
1. Enable Speed Insights in the Vercel dashboard for this project
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. After deployment and user visits, performance metrics will be available in the Speed Insights dashboard

## Technical Notes
- The SpeedInsights component automatically handles client-side performance tracking
- No additional configuration is needed for basic functionality
- The component is designed to have minimal impact on application performance
- Works seamlessly with Next.js server and client components
